<task id="AUTHV2-047" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix appsettings.template.json — env-specific placeholders</title>
    <phase>C — Server hardening</phase>
    <tags>auth, server, config, env-independence, MINIMAL</tags>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>C-Parallel-2</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Two config issues in appsettings.template.json: (1) AzureAd:TenantId is hardcoded "common" — should be #{TENANT_ID}#. (2) AgentToken:CopilotAudience hardcoded UUID `auth-3e04ab58-...` — should be parameterized.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET engineer.</role>
  <goal>Template uses placeholders for all env-specific values. New customer-tenant deployment requires only placeholder substitution.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.template.json (lines 36, 226)</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §3 M-2, M-3</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Edit appsettings.template.json: line 36 change `"TenantId": "common"` to `"TenantId": "#{TENANT_ID}#"`.</step>
    <step>Line 226: change `"CopilotAudience": "api://auth-3e04ab58-8450-44d6-b95b-daca16b6cbdb/#{API_APP_ID}#"` to `"CopilotAudience": "api://#{COPILOT_SSO_PROVIDER_APP_ID}#/#{API_APP_ID}#"`.</step>
    <step>Update deployment script (scripts/deploy-bff-api.ps1 or similar) to substitute COPILOT_SSO_PROVIDER_APP_ID from a parameter.</step>
    <step>Update deployment parameter docs (env files, README) to add the new variable.</step>
    <step>Re-deploy to dev and verify nothing broke.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>No hardcoded "common" or UUIDs in appsettings.template.json for env-specific values.</criterion>
    <criterion>Deployment script substitutes the new placeholders.</criterion>
    <criterion>Dev deployment works with new template.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes>
Completed 2026-05-19 (parallel Phase C wave; sibling sub-agents executing 043, 044, 045, 046, 048).

**Files modified:**
- `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.template.json`
  - Line 36: `"TenantId": "common"` → `"TenantId": "#{TENANT_ID}#"` (M-2 fix)
  - Line 226: `"CopilotAudience": "api://auth-3e04ab58-8450-44d6-b95b-daca16b6cbdb/#{API_APP_ID}#"` → `"CopilotAudience": "api://#{COPILOT_SSO_PROVIDER_APP_ID}#/#{API_APP_ID}#"` (M-3 fix)
- `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.tokens.md`
  - Added `#{COPILOT_SSO_PROVIDER_APP_ID}#` and `#{COPILOT_AGENT_APP_ID}#` to the token reference table
  - Added them to the "Development Values" example block
  - Added a "Notes" section explaining the historical UUID and providing the default value (`auth-3e04ab58-8450-44d6-b95b-daca16b6cbdb`) for CI/CD pipelines that don't override

**Placeholder format used:** `#{TOKEN_NAME}#` — matches existing convention documented in `appsettings.tokens.md` and used throughout the template (compatible with Azure DevOps `FileTransform@2` and GitHub Actions `cschleiden/replace-tokens`).

**Step 3 (deployment script update) — NOT required:** `Deploy-BffApi.ps1` does NOT do placeholder substitution. Per `appsettings.tokens.md`, substitution happens in the CI/CD pipeline (Azure DevOps File Transform or GitHub Actions replace-tokens action) BEFORE `dotnet publish`. The deploy script only builds + packages + deploys + verifies. Substitution is configured via environment-specific variable registries that read from `appsettings.tokens.md`. **Operator action required for next deploy:** add `COPILOT_SSO_PROVIDER_APP_ID=auth-3e04ab58-8450-44d6-b95b-daca16b6cbdb` to the dev + prod pipeline variable sets. (For dev, this can also live in App Service config as `AgentToken__CopilotAudience` Key Vault reference — bypassing template substitution entirely.)

**Step 5 (re-deploy + verify) — DEFERRED:** Out of scope for this sub-agent per parallel-execution rules (DO NOT commit, DO NOT touch outside `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`). To be done after Phase C waves consolidate.

**Build verification:** `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — pre-existing build break in `AuthorizationModule.cs:49,56` (missing `AuthSchemes` symbol) from sibling agent task 045 WIP. NOT caused by this task. JSON template file is not a compile input; `appsettings.tokens.md` is documentation. My changes have zero compile impact.

**JSON validity verified:** Template parses cleanly after simulated CI substitution (booleans → `true`, strings → `placeholder`).

**Audit by-product (NOT in scope for this task — flag for future hardening):**
Other hardcoded values in `appsettings.template.json` reviewed: `BingSearch:Endpoint`, `LlamaParse:BaseUrl`, `AiSearch:*IndexName/SemanticConfigName/ApiKeySecretName`, `AzureOpenAI:EmbeddingModelName/ClassificationModelName`. All are service constants (universal endpoints or Spaarke-internal naming conventions shared across deployments), not env-specific tenant values. No M-grade audit findings against them. Out of scope.
  </notes>
</task>
